page.title: 01Ullingswick N E of Hereford
page.content:
The area is mainly agricultural, with very few services and only scattered builings. In north and west if mainly grazing, in the south and east more cultivated farmland.
An industrial frm dominates south west corner, there are small workshops making farm gates and prefabricated barns in south east
Ullingswick is a sprawling village, with no real centre. Some nw houses built to the south west have exagerated this trend, as have the small lanes which serve as roads. A post office exists but is very difficult to find unless you already know of its locatoin
